							<div class="bio-container">
					<div class="bio-img-container">
						<div class="bio-img">
							<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/angela-rodel-aubg-board-of-trustees-100x100.png" width="96" height="96" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/angela-rodel-aubg-board-of-trustees-300x300.png 2x" alt="Angela Rodel" class="avatar avatar-96 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-96 alignnone photo" />						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Angela Rodel</h4>
												<p>Angela Rodel is a literary translator who holds degrees from Yale and UCLA in linguistics and ethnomusicology. Eight Bulgarian novels in her translation have been published in the US and UK. She has received NEA and PEN translation grants, including an NEA grant for her translation of <em>The Case of Cem</em>. Her translation of Georgi Gospodinov’s <em>Physics of Sorrow</em> won the 2016 AATSEEL Prize for Literary Translation, and her translation of his novel <em>Time Shelter</em> won the 2023 International Booker Prize. A two-time Fulbright scholar, she now lives in Sofia, Bulgaria, where she serves as executive director of the Bulgarian-American Fulbright Commission.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			
